WEBVTT

00:02.502 --> 00:04.271
Thank you, kids,
for taking a break

00:04.271 --> 00:06.840
from your reading,
gaming, and...

00:06.840 --> 00:08.242
Pyrokinesis.

00:09.877 --> 00:10.911
Nothing yet.

00:10.911 --> 00:12.513
Right.

00:12.513 --> 00:14.281
Now, as you all know, the work
starts today on the house.

00:14.281 --> 00:16.950
Can we get an underground mall,
like Barbra Streisand has?

00:16.950 --> 00:18.051
Why do you know that?

00:18.051 --> 00:19.353
There is no one
who covets

00:19.353 --> 00:20.954
a subterranean Cinnabon
more than me,

00:20.954 --> 00:22.856
but I'm pretty sure it would be
a permitting nightmare.

00:22.856 --> 00:25.125
In addition to the presence
of workers,

00:25.125 --> 00:27.294
there might be migrant
dust particles and VOCs,

00:27.294 --> 00:29.263
which I will be doing my best
to shield you from.

00:29.263 --> 00:30.898
So, we are selling?

00:30.898 --> 00:32.266
No, we are fixing.

00:32.266 --> 00:34.067
Because things need
to be fixed.

00:34.067 --> 00:35.669
And that is all.

00:35.669 --> 00:36.904
For now.

00:36.904 --> 00:38.572
Oh, we are headed straight
for apartment city.

00:38.572 --> 00:41.041
I can already hear
the upstairs neighbors.

00:41.041 --> 00:42.442
Mom, no.

00:42.442 --> 00:44.311
I wouldn't flourish
in an apartment setting.

00:44.311 --> 00:45.546
You know that about me.

00:45.546 --> 00:47.681
I have always wanted
a doorman.

00:47.681 --> 00:50.918
No doorman, no apartment city,
just repairs.

00:50.918 --> 00:52.452
Ohh...

00:52.452 --> 00:54.021
Now, Vlad and his men are gonna
be here any minute,

00:54.021 --> 00:57.057
so let's not set anyone on fire
with our minds, okay?

00:57.057 --> 00:58.392
The easier we make it
on them,

00:58.392 --> 01:00.093
the more
efficiently they'll work,

01:00.093 --> 01:02.229
and the sooner
they will go away.

01:02.229 --> 01:04.298
[ Doorbell rings ]

01:04.298 --> 01:06.566
If we just had that doorman.

01:08.302 --> 01:10.537
Welcome! Welcome.
Welcome to you.

01:10.537 --> 01:13.507
Please come in but stay only
on the path I've fashioned

01:13.507 --> 01:15.375
to help curtail the spread
of your debris.

01:15.375 --> 01:17.010
Vladislav: Wow.

01:17.010 --> 01:19.479
You -- You really rolled out
the paper carpet for us, huh?

01:19.479 --> 01:21.515
Well, I'm just trying to make
both our lives easier.

01:21.515 --> 01:24.217
Thank you for restricting
our movements.

01:24.217 --> 01:25.218
Here's the good news.

01:25.218 --> 01:26.653
At the end of the paper path,

01:26.653 --> 01:28.488
you'll find
a refreshment station

01:28.488 --> 01:30.324
featuring a light
continental breakfast.

01:30.324 --> 01:32.326
Today's selection is fresh,
hot waffles.

01:32.326 --> 01:35.262
What I really need right now
is Ee-van.

01:35.262 --> 01:36.563
Ee-van?

01:36.563 --> 01:37.664
Ivan. John.

01:37.664 --> 01:39.333
Your John.

01:39.333 --> 01:42.469
I had a bochka of coffee
on the way here, so...

01:42.469 --> 01:43.837
[ Sighs ]

01:43.837 --> 01:45.305
...nature calls.

01:45.305 --> 01:47.341
Seriously, you guys don't come
with your own facilities?

01:47.341 --> 01:50.477
I have a call in to a guy.

01:50.477 --> 01:53.480
Right now, I just need your --
your bathroom...

01:53.480 --> 01:57.184
and your --
your Wi-Fi password.

01:57.184 --> 01:59.386
Password.

01:59.386 --> 02:01.254
The password is "password".

02:01.254 --> 02:02.756
♪♪

02:02.756 --> 02:06.259
♪ Keep giving me hope
for a better day ♪

02:06.259 --> 02:09.429
♪ Keep giving me love
to find a way ♪

02:09.429 --> 02:12.699
♪ Through this heaviness
I feel ♪

02:12.699 --> 02:19.139
♪ I just need someone to say
everything's okay ♪

02:19.139 --> 02:21.208
♪ Everything's okay ♪

02:21.208 --> 02:23.076
-- Captions by VITAC --

02:23.076 --> 02:25.145
[ Telephone ringing ]

02:25.145 --> 02:28.148
[ Mouse clicking ]

02:28.148 --> 02:30.584
Marty McFly,
how goes it?

02:30.584 --> 02:32.619
Come on, Holly.
I hate when you call me that.

02:32.619 --> 02:36.123
Okay, don't get all Martin Short
with me.

02:36.123 --> 02:37.457
Did I catch you
at a bad time?

02:37.457 --> 02:38.825
You looking at porn?

02:38.825 --> 02:41.628
Pretty hot for these bespoke
adventure vans.

02:41.628 --> 02:42.863
Take a look.

02:42.863 --> 02:46.199
Camping with a full kitchen
and a flat screen.

02:46.199 --> 02:48.235
Good Lord, you've gone soft
on me.

02:48.235 --> 02:49.236
What, me?!

02:49.236 --> 02:50.604
Mm.
No.

02:50.604 --> 02:53.040
Who's gonna tell ya
if not your work wife?

02:53.040 --> 02:54.574
I was looking
at the perk board.

02:54.574 --> 02:57.477
You've got three months' worth
of unused "Play Days"!

02:57.477 --> 02:58.211
I do?

02:58.211 --> 02:59.980
You do.

02:59.980 --> 03:01.314
[ Sighs ]

03:01.314 --> 03:04.117
Seize the play.

03:04.117 --> 03:05.886
Play Day.

03:05.886 --> 03:07.888
Arthur: Is that where they
trick you into working hard

03:07.888 --> 03:09.289
by making it sound fun?

03:09.289 --> 03:11.158
No, those are
Hooray Days.

03:11.158 --> 03:12.993
Yeah.
Ooh! Those do sound fun!

03:12.993 --> 03:15.262
Yeah, Play Days are paid
vacation that have to be spent

03:15.262 --> 03:16.697
doing something outdoorsy.

03:16.697 --> 03:18.565
I used to take full advantage
of mine,

03:18.565 --> 03:20.867
but Lena always hated
the camping.

03:20.867 --> 03:21.968
She nay'ed my play

03:21.968 --> 03:25.138
until one day, you know,
I just stopped going.

03:25.138 --> 03:26.473
That's so sad.

03:26.473 --> 03:27.941
[ Whispering ]
I hate that story.

03:27.941 --> 03:30.243
Marriage has a sneaky way of
making you change the parts

03:30.243 --> 03:31.678
of yourself
that you value most.

03:31.678 --> 03:34.214
I know. Camille's making me
get adult braces,

03:34.214 --> 03:35.882
and my teeth
are completely fine.

03:35.882 --> 03:36.550
Let me see these.

03:36.550 --> 03:37.751
What? They're beautiful!

03:37.751 --> 03:39.352
Thank you.

03:39.352 --> 03:40.921
Maybe it's time
we put our foot down.

03:40.921 --> 03:42.255
Maybe!

03:42.255 --> 03:44.157
I'll be honest,
I don't intend to.

03:44.157 --> 03:45.525
I already have my molar bands.

03:45.525 --> 03:47.494
No, I was really just talking
about my thing.

03:47.494 --> 03:48.695
The great outdoors, man.

03:48.695 --> 03:49.496
Yes!

03:49.496 --> 03:50.897
Yes. You should come!

03:50.897 --> 03:52.499
No!
Come on!

03:52.499 --> 03:54.301
Come on. Don't you want to know
how freeing it is

03:54.301 --> 03:55.802
to only worry about survival?

03:55.802 --> 03:58.605
Don't you want to prove that you
can make it off the grid?

03:58.605 --> 04:00.540
Not really.
I love the grid.

04:00.540 --> 04:02.075
The grid charges my Tesla.

04:02.075 --> 04:04.010
[ Tango music plays ]

04:04.010 --> 04:07.447
♪♪

04:07.447 --> 04:10.317
No, no, I got it.

04:10.317 --> 04:12.519
Don't worry about it.
Just throw it anywhere.

04:12.519 --> 04:14.721
Oh, no, here's good.

04:14.721 --> 04:16.389
Martin!

04:16.389 --> 04:17.991
Can you believe this?

04:17.991 --> 04:19.226
Believe what?

04:19.226 --> 04:21.361
They're treating our house
like a dump.

04:21.361 --> 04:23.230
There's debris everywhere.

04:23.230 --> 04:24.397
Of course there's debris.

04:24.397 --> 04:25.232
They're working.

04:25.232 --> 04:26.500
Are they?

04:26.500 --> 04:28.135
Because it looks like
they're having coffee

04:28.135 --> 04:29.736
and eating burgers.

04:29.736 --> 04:32.405
Mm, well, maybe if you hadn't
set up that waffle kiosk.

04:32.405 --> 04:33.540
So you're not gonna say
anything?

04:33.540 --> 04:35.809
Nope.
Got it. Per usual, it's on me.

04:35.809 --> 04:36.910
Yep.

04:39.312 --> 04:40.447
Vlad.

04:40.447 --> 04:42.349
You got a second to talk shop?

04:42.349 --> 04:43.683
Vladislav: Sure.

04:43.683 --> 04:45.018
I hear there's a sale
at Bloomingdale's.

04:45.018 --> 04:46.386
Ha, ha, ha, ha.

04:46.386 --> 04:48.355
We've got a regular
Yakov Smirnoff over here.

04:48.355 --> 04:52.826
You mean it as a burn, but I
take it as a great compliment.

04:52.826 --> 04:55.996
So, I'm hoping that after you
finish your coffee klatch,

04:55.996 --> 04:58.965
you and Carl's Junior are gonna
get around to tidying up

04:58.965 --> 05:00.800
and dealing
with my foundation?

05:00.800 --> 05:02.969
That's the plan.
What's the plan?

05:02.969 --> 05:04.938
What you just said.

05:04.938 --> 05:08.708
Okay, look, I am going to need
some real information,

05:08.708 --> 05:11.978
and I want you to figure out
the root of the problem.

05:11.978 --> 05:13.180
I know the root.

05:13.180 --> 05:15.582
♪♪

05:15.582 --> 05:17.050
You gonna tell me?

05:17.050 --> 05:18.885
Sure.
It's wet.

05:18.885 --> 05:19.653
What's wet?

05:19.653 --> 05:21.521
The, uh, crawl space.

05:21.521 --> 05:23.924
The soil.
There's moisture.

05:23.924 --> 05:25.058
Vlad, hear me.

05:25.058 --> 05:28.495
I vent. I dehumidify.
I'm doing my part.

05:28.495 --> 05:29.696
Your dirt is still damp.

05:29.696 --> 05:32.532
My dirt is still damp?

05:32.532 --> 05:34.301
You're gonna look me
in the eye

05:34.301 --> 05:38.038
and tell me my dirt
is still damp?

05:38.038 --> 05:41.041
Your dirt is still damp.

05:41.041 --> 05:43.610
I told husband.
Okay, don't tell husband.

05:43.610 --> 05:45.612
Tell me.
Husband doesn't care.

05:45.612 --> 05:47.647
I'm here, I'm front and center.
I'm --

05:47.647 --> 05:49.482
Geological engineer?

05:49.482 --> 05:51.818
I'm emotionally
invested, Vlad.

05:51.818 --> 05:53.019
Hmm.

05:53.019 --> 05:56.623
So, tell me, how do we take care
of the moisture?

05:56.623 --> 05:58.558
Finish the crawl space.

06:00.193 --> 06:01.761
You talking vapor barrier?

06:01.761 --> 06:03.630
That could be one
of the solutions, yes.

06:03.630 --> 06:04.731
Was that a smirk?

06:04.731 --> 06:06.199
Not a smirk --
just my face.

06:06.199 --> 06:07.734
It looked like a smirk.

06:07.734 --> 06:09.236
Face.

06:09.236 --> 06:11.438
[ Sighs ]
Think of it.

06:11.438 --> 06:15.208
24 hours of camping,
fishing, and hunting.

06:15.208 --> 06:17.110
Can I start the fire?

06:17.110 --> 06:18.311
What?

06:18.311 --> 06:19.546
No. Forget it.

06:19.546 --> 06:21.615
You said that...weird.

06:25.318 --> 06:27.420
[ Sighs ]

06:27.420 --> 06:28.388
Let's hear it.

06:28.388 --> 06:29.889
Dance for me.

06:29.889 --> 06:31.625
Uh, Wiccan.

06:31.625 --> 06:33.860
Uh, uh, Lilith-journals.

06:33.860 --> 06:35.262
Ani DiFranco.

06:35.262 --> 06:38.064
Um...birds.
Birds?

06:38.064 --> 06:39.266
Ugh!

06:39.266 --> 06:40.400
Where's Mason?

06:40.400 --> 06:41.668
Upstairs drowning
in self-pity.

06:41.668 --> 06:43.937
[ Sighs ]
Still with the Hazel breakup?

06:43.937 --> 06:46.139
Pretty clear she made
the right choice.

06:46.139 --> 06:47.474
Am I right?

06:47.474 --> 06:48.308
[ Sighs ]

06:48.308 --> 06:50.543
Mace, hey.

06:50.543 --> 06:52.412
I get where you're
at right now, bud.

06:52.412 --> 06:55.215
I really do.

06:55.215 --> 06:56.616
I've been there myself.

06:56.616 --> 06:58.218
But trust me, it's not gonna
make you feel any better

06:58.218 --> 07:00.253
to stay cooped up
in your room all weekend,

07:00.253 --> 07:01.721
sucking at video games.

07:01.721 --> 07:03.556
He's not gonna be cooped up
in his room all weekend.

07:03.556 --> 07:04.991
It's Curls Night.

07:04.991 --> 07:05.992
What?

07:05.992 --> 07:07.394
Tomorrow,
it's Curls Night Out!

07:07.394 --> 07:08.895
It is?
I put it on the calendar.

07:08.895 --> 07:10.897
What the hell's
a Curls Night Out?

07:10.897 --> 07:13.900
Every so often, me,
Mae, and Mason --

07:13.900 --> 07:15.702
you know, everyone
with curly hair --

07:15.702 --> 07:18.571
we go out on the town,
just us curls.

07:18.571 --> 07:20.173
We get a sitter for Milo.

07:20.173 --> 07:21.241
Curls Night Out?!

07:21.241 --> 07:22.375
No!

07:22.375 --> 07:23.977
No, no! Absolutely not!

07:23.977 --> 07:27.047
Our son is on the cusp
of becoming a man, Lena!

07:27.047 --> 07:28.948
We need to nurture
his virility,

07:28.948 --> 07:33.019
teach him how to be confident
and strong, not emasculate him.

07:33.019 --> 07:36.356
Last time we saw "Dear Evan
Hansen" and went to Sephora.

07:36.356 --> 07:37.791
I-It was pretty lit.

07:37.791 --> 07:38.892
Yeah.

07:38.892 --> 07:41.461
You know what's really
gonna be lit, Mace?

07:41.461 --> 07:43.129
Our campfire.

07:43.129 --> 07:44.331
When we go camping.

07:44.331 --> 07:45.965
This weekend.

07:45.965 --> 07:47.067
Huh?

07:47.067 --> 07:48.201
Right, bud?

07:48.201 --> 07:49.669
I-I guess...

07:49.669 --> 07:52.305
Whoa!
It's not your weekend!

07:52.305 --> 07:53.340
Oh, that's right.

07:53.340 --> 07:54.574
It's not.

07:54.574 --> 07:56.609
That's why I'm going camping
in the woods,

07:56.609 --> 07:59.446
and I'm inviting our big, strong
son to come with me!

07:59.446 --> 08:01.614
Come on!

08:01.614 --> 08:02.816
No pressure from me, Mace.

08:02.816 --> 08:05.385
You do whatever you want.

08:05.385 --> 08:10.757
♪♪

08:10.757 --> 08:13.026
I-I guess I'll go with Dad?

08:13.026 --> 08:16.229
That's my boy!
Yeaaahhh!

08:16.229 --> 08:17.597
Whoo-hoo-hoo!

08:17.597 --> 08:18.832
"Play Day" in full effect!

08:18.832 --> 08:20.700
Alright,
we'll miss you, Curl.

08:20.700 --> 08:23.436
We are going to own
the outdoors, man!

08:23.436 --> 08:28.108
We are going to show the wild
that we are strong, capable men!

08:28.108 --> 08:29.576
♪♪

08:33.613 --> 08:36.316
[ Toilet flushes ]

08:36.316 --> 08:39.119
How far away are we
from installing the flooring?

08:39.119 --> 08:40.153
Good morning.

08:40.153 --> 08:41.554
Oh, I'm sorry.

08:41.554 --> 08:43.656
Did you want pleasantries?

08:43.656 --> 08:46.326
How was your 18th dump
in my bathroom?

08:46.326 --> 08:47.961
You're a real charmer.

08:50.463 --> 08:52.132
Let's talk flooring.

08:52.132 --> 08:56.202
So, I did a little independent
research, and the experts say

08:56.202 --> 08:59.406
flooring needs to breathe
for 10 days before install.

08:59.406 --> 09:01.107
Wow, you're so good
at this.

09:01.107 --> 09:01.841
Home repairs?

09:01.841 --> 09:03.710
Eh, making people miserable.

09:03.710 --> 09:05.345
She's gonna buckle, Vlad.

09:05.345 --> 09:07.847
You install that wood
without letting her acclimate,

09:07.847 --> 09:09.315
and we both know
she's gonna buckle.

09:16.423 --> 09:18.024
Did you learn Russian?

09:18.024 --> 09:18.958
A little.

09:18.958 --> 09:20.026
Huh.

09:20.026 --> 09:22.128
Well, I beg you,
please let me do my job.

09:22.128 --> 09:24.330
All you have to do is just sit
there and look pretty.

09:24.330 --> 09:27.567
In this country, women don't
take that as a compliment.

09:27.567 --> 09:28.968
And correct me
if I'm wrong,

09:28.968 --> 09:30.837
but you would never speak
to a man that way.

09:30.837 --> 09:32.005
Because I never
get a chance to!

09:32.005 --> 09:33.506
Where is the man
of the house?!

09:33.506 --> 09:35.708
Because frankly, I would rather
be communicating with him.

09:35.708 --> 09:37.410
Well, you're looking
at him, baby!

09:37.410 --> 09:41.414
As far as you're concerned,
I am the man of the house.

09:41.414 --> 09:45.518
♪♪

09:45.518 --> 09:46.820
Martin: Alright.

09:46.820 --> 09:50.190
This looks pretty good.
Good ground coverage.

09:50.190 --> 09:51.591
Ah, this is it.

09:51.591 --> 09:53.860
[ Grunts ]

09:53.860 --> 09:56.095
[ Exhales deeply ]

09:56.095 --> 09:58.932
♪♪

09:58.932 --> 10:00.066
Oh.

10:00.066 --> 10:02.869
Ice-cold water
after a long, sweaty hike,

10:02.869 --> 10:06.172
I tell ya, that's the best taste
in the world.

10:06.172 --> 10:07.707
You thirsty, Mace?

10:10.443 --> 10:11.644
What the hell, man?

10:11.644 --> 10:14.414
I'm sticky
and I'm sweaty.

10:14.414 --> 10:15.582
I need to take a shower.

10:15.582 --> 10:16.583
A shower?!

10:16.583 --> 10:18.618
[ Scoffs ] We're camping.

10:18.618 --> 10:20.420
Does that mean
we can't wash?

10:20.420 --> 10:21.788
[ Scoffs ] I mean...

10:21.788 --> 10:24.457
I guess you could wash
in the stream.

10:24.457 --> 10:25.625
Okay, perfect.

10:25.625 --> 10:26.993
Just...do me a favor

10:26.993 --> 10:29.095
and take off that ridiculous
shower hat, okay?

10:29.095 --> 10:31.364
I don't want the wildlife
laughing at you.

10:31.364 --> 10:33.766
[ Woodpecker tapping,
birds chirping ]

10:33.766 --> 10:34.901
What's wrong?

10:34.901 --> 10:36.436
I don't want to
take it off.

10:36.436 --> 10:37.971
What? Why?

10:37.971 --> 10:41.207
I don't like it when wet hair
lays against my head.

10:41.207 --> 10:41.941
It squeeves me.

10:41.941 --> 10:44.010
It squeeves you?

10:44.010 --> 10:46.379
Since when?
Since always.

10:46.379 --> 10:47.814
What about swimming?

10:47.814 --> 10:48.882
I don't go under.

10:48.882 --> 10:50.183
You never go under?

10:50.183 --> 10:52.519
Unless I have access
to a hairdryer,

10:52.519 --> 10:55.388
which I'm assuming
we don't?

10:55.388 --> 10:56.956
We don't.

10:56.956 --> 11:00.326
So, this weekend, I'm just not
gonna get my hair wet, okay?

11:00.326 --> 11:01.761
Okay.

11:01.761 --> 11:03.663
I guess.

11:03.663 --> 11:05.532
I'm sorry
if I'm disappointing you.

11:05.532 --> 11:06.666
[ Sighs ] No.

11:06.666 --> 11:07.767
No. No, no, no.

11:07.767 --> 11:09.802
[ Chuckles ]
You're not, buddy.

11:09.802 --> 11:10.870
You're fine.

11:10.870 --> 11:13.506
You know what, you're great.

11:13.506 --> 11:15.375
Why don't you go freshen up...

11:15.375 --> 11:19.612
in your bonnet, and, uh,
then we'll make camp, alright?

11:19.612 --> 11:21.514
Okay.

11:21.514 --> 11:22.682
[ Sighs ]

11:22.682 --> 11:25.151
Yeah. Yeah.
Can't forget that.

11:25.151 --> 11:28.688
♪♪

11:28.688 --> 11:30.290
[ Conversation in Russian ]

11:30.290 --> 11:34.427
♪♪

11:34.427 --> 11:36.629
[ Laughter ]

11:36.629 --> 11:38.364
Man:
Forget about the flooring.

11:38.364 --> 11:40.466
It's the lady
who needs to get laid!

11:40.466 --> 11:41.901
[ Laughter ]

11:41.901 --> 11:43.336
Lena: Believe you me,
they were not talking

11:43.336 --> 11:45.371
about my maple hardwood,
which, incidentally,

11:45.371 --> 11:47.774
I had to order
from two separate venders

11:47.774 --> 11:49.342
and pay twice the shipping.

11:49.342 --> 11:50.076
You told me.

11:50.076 --> 11:51.344
Martin's the one who decided

11:51.344 --> 11:53.046
we were gonna do
these home repairs,

11:53.046 --> 11:55.748
but I'm gonna wind up navigating
the whole thing solo.

11:55.748 --> 11:58.451
What if you don't
navigate it?

11:58.451 --> 12:00.386
[ Laughs ]
We shall see.

12:00.386 --> 12:02.388
What do you think happens
when I'm out of Vlad's hair

12:02.388 --> 12:03.856
for a minute?

12:03.856 --> 12:05.191
Nothing.

12:05.191 --> 12:06.025
Not a thing.

12:06.025 --> 12:07.393
That's exactly right.

12:07.393 --> 12:08.494
She gets it!

12:08.494 --> 12:10.029
Noooo, I don't.

12:10.029 --> 12:13.333
Look, it's, um -- it's dawning
on me very, very clearly now,

12:13.333 --> 12:14.767
and I'd be remiss
if I didn't say it --

12:14.767 --> 12:17.470
you do need
to get laid.

12:17.470 --> 12:19.172
Come again?

12:19.172 --> 12:21.207
Look, I think you're so focused
on these stupid house repairs,

12:21.207 --> 12:22.875
you're neglecting
your self-care.

12:22.875 --> 12:24.544
I self-care!

12:24.544 --> 12:26.512
Every other week when I have
access to the tub.

12:26.512 --> 12:29.682
Okay, look, it just feels like
you're directing

12:29.682 --> 12:33.953
your frustrations
at this Russian contractor guy.

12:33.953 --> 12:36.522
You need to get out of the house
for a minute.

12:36.522 --> 12:38.758
Go have your own "Play Day."

12:38.758 --> 12:40.493
[ Birds chirping ]

12:40.493 --> 12:42.528
♪♪

12:42.528 --> 12:47.500
[ Cellphone buttons clicking ]

12:47.500 --> 12:50.003
[ Message sends ]

12:50.003 --> 12:52.672
Martin: Isn't this cool?

12:52.672 --> 12:55.908
We're hunting for dinner,
just like our forefathers did.

12:55.908 --> 12:57.677
Yeah, or...

12:57.677 --> 13:00.947
we could just eat Wheat Thins
like our foremothers packed.

13:00.947 --> 13:03.549
Hey, you know what would go
great on those?

13:03.549 --> 13:05.151
Fresh hunk of deer.

13:06.986 --> 13:08.655
[ Whispering ]
Oh, whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa, okay.

13:08.655 --> 13:10.590
Shh, shh, shh, shh, shh,

13:10.590 --> 13:12.358
Come on, baby.

13:12.358 --> 13:15.294
[ Sighs ]
Come on, baby.

13:15.294 --> 13:20.466
♪♪

13:20.466 --> 13:22.268
Run!
Oh!

13:22.268 --> 13:23.436
Dude.

13:23.436 --> 13:24.570
What the hell?

13:24.570 --> 13:25.672
I-I'm sorry, okay?

13:25.672 --> 13:26.939
I-I-I...
I just...

13:26.939 --> 13:27.940
I don't want to
kill animals.

13:27.940 --> 13:29.308
But I was gonna kill it.

13:29.308 --> 13:31.944
Well, I don't want you
to kill it either, okay?

13:31.944 --> 13:33.880
[ Sighs ]
So I gave him a heads-up.

13:33.880 --> 13:35.348
Cool, yeah,
good looking out, Mace...

13:35.348 --> 13:38.651
for that deer,
I mean, 'cause us?

13:38.651 --> 13:41.254
We don't have dinner.

13:41.254 --> 13:44.190
♪♪

13:44.190 --> 13:47.260
Man, I bet those curls
are two Shirleys deep by now.

13:47.260 --> 13:49.128
♪♪

13:49.128 --> 13:50.363
[ Sighing ] Oh, man.

13:50.363 --> 13:51.731
Wes:
[ Exhales deeply, chuckles ]

13:51.731 --> 13:55.635
That is what they call
a "nooner."

13:55.635 --> 13:57.236
Was that a "nooner"?

13:57.236 --> 13:58.705
Or does "nooner" mean
something else?

13:58.705 --> 14:03.476
No, that -- that definitely
qualifies as a "nooner."

14:03.476 --> 14:04.610
A late nooner?

14:04.610 --> 14:06.412
[ Chuckles ]

14:06.412 --> 14:07.780
Mmm.

14:07.780 --> 14:09.615
Oh, God.
[ Sighs ]

14:09.615 --> 14:11.217
I really have to thank you.

14:11.217 --> 14:13.986
I think you just saved my life.

14:13.986 --> 14:15.988
[ Sighs ] Is there some way
I can repay you?

14:15.988 --> 14:17.890
Hmm?
I make a killer omelette...

14:17.890 --> 14:19.459
Um...

14:19.459 --> 14:22.662
Sorry, I -- I feel like that
might irritate my girlfriend.

14:22.662 --> 14:23.996
Your girlfriend?

14:23.996 --> 14:25.631
You still have a girlfriend?

14:25.631 --> 14:26.899
Yeah, Meegan.

14:26.899 --> 14:29.736
And the omelette
would annoy her?

14:29.736 --> 14:31.404
We just had sex.

14:31.404 --> 14:34.607
I know, but we're poly.
Poly?

14:34.607 --> 14:37.577
We're allowed to experience
intimacy with other people,

14:37.577 --> 14:39.479
but we always try to have dinner
with each other.

14:39.479 --> 14:41.080
Meegan: Helloooo...

14:41.080 --> 14:43.015
[ Gasps ] Hi!

14:43.015 --> 14:45.952
Wow, afternoon delight!

14:45.952 --> 14:46.886
Yum, yum, yum!

14:46.886 --> 14:47.754
[ Chuckles ]

14:47.754 --> 14:49.021
Yes!

14:49.021 --> 14:50.757
Ooh, I want bites.
I want bites.

14:50.757 --> 14:51.958
Yum, yum, yum,
give me bites.

14:51.958 --> 14:52.825
Gimme, gimme.

14:52.825 --> 14:54.060
[ Laughter ]

14:54.060 --> 14:57.130
Look at you.
Natural beauty.

14:57.130 --> 14:58.297
You look so familiar.

14:58.297 --> 14:59.432
We actually --
We met at the --

14:59.432 --> 15:00.867
Ooh, ooh, ooh,
don't tell me.

15:00.867 --> 15:03.503
I'm so good at guessing.
Let me guess.

15:03.503 --> 15:05.071
[ Gasps ]

15:05.071 --> 15:06.672
Do you work for the DWP?

15:06.672 --> 15:07.907
I do not.

15:07.907 --> 15:09.075
Have you waxed me?

15:09.075 --> 15:10.276
Are you my waxer?

15:10.276 --> 15:14.747
No.
Your face is triggering me.

15:14.747 --> 15:16.783
Are you Maura Tierney?

15:16.783 --> 15:18.718
From "The Affair"?

15:18.718 --> 15:19.919
No.

15:19.919 --> 15:20.987
Okay, but do you watch
"The Affair"?

15:20.987 --> 15:22.488
No.
Have you binged it?

15:22.488 --> 15:23.723
[ Silly voice ]
It's super bingeable.

15:23.723 --> 15:24.891
Did you binge it?

15:24.891 --> 15:25.825
Because it's bingeable,
hello.

15:25.825 --> 15:26.659
Babe, babe, she's my --

15:26.659 --> 15:27.660
I'm the deli lady.

15:27.660 --> 15:28.961
I'm his deli lady,

15:28.961 --> 15:32.398
and I came by to drop off
some light capicola.

15:32.398 --> 15:33.533
And Swiss.

15:33.533 --> 15:35.668
I'm gonna kill you!
Did you eat without me?!

15:35.668 --> 15:37.804
No! No!
Oh, my --

15:37.804 --> 15:39.539
No?
No.

15:39.539 --> 15:40.673
Okay. [ Laughs ]

15:40.673 --> 15:42.675
[ Chuckles ]

15:42.675 --> 15:43.843
Bye, Maura Tierney.

15:43.843 --> 15:44.844
Bye.

15:44.844 --> 15:45.344
See you, Maura.
Bye.

15:49.982 --> 15:51.150
You see?
Okay, great, now pull it taut --

15:51.150 --> 15:52.518
more, more, more, more,
very good.

15:52.518 --> 15:53.920
Okay, now drive it
into the ground right there.

15:53.920 --> 15:55.488
There you go.
Perfect.

15:55.488 --> 15:57.190
Now step on it hard.

15:58.958 --> 16:00.059
[ Stake snaps ]

16:00.059 --> 16:01.794
Uh,
I think I broke it...

16:01.794 --> 16:03.162
What?
You couldn't have.

16:03.162 --> 16:04.964
I messed it up.

16:04.964 --> 16:06.699
Like I mess everything up.

16:06.699 --> 16:07.700
No wonder she left me.

16:07.700 --> 16:09.702
[ Sighs ]

16:09.702 --> 16:11.070
She didn't leave you.

16:11.070 --> 16:12.338
She walked out on me.

16:12.338 --> 16:14.507
Walked out where,
to the gymnasium?

16:14.507 --> 16:16.142
I mean, you --
you weren't living together.

16:16.142 --> 16:17.610
You're teenagers.

16:17.610 --> 16:19.111
Okay, I know you're all ready
for me to get over Hazel,

16:19.111 --> 16:21.547
but I-I just can't yet.

16:21.547 --> 16:22.248
Okay, I-I get it.

16:22.248 --> 16:23.749
Okay, I-I get it.

16:23.749 --> 16:25.885
She -- She hurt your ego,
she wounded your pride.

16:25.885 --> 16:27.220
No.

16:27.220 --> 16:29.388
I-I don't care about either
of those things.

16:29.388 --> 16:32.525
She hurt my heart,
and I'm -- I'm sorry,

16:32.525 --> 16:36.295
but I-I still love Hazel,
even if she doesn't love me.

16:38.097 --> 16:40.933
Right, right.

16:40.933 --> 16:43.269
Right, I-I --
yeah, but you gotta...

16:43.269 --> 16:45.104
[ Sighs ] You know, you got to
pick yourself up

16:45.104 --> 16:48.140
by the bootstraps,
don't you?

16:48.140 --> 16:50.509
You gotta soldier on.

16:50.509 --> 16:51.744
Why?

16:51.744 --> 16:53.312
I'm not in the military.

16:53.312 --> 16:54.981
I'm in high school.

16:54.981 --> 16:57.617
I-I want to feel
all my feelings.

16:57.617 --> 16:59.819
Like Drake.

16:59.819 --> 17:02.021
I'm -- I'm sure the same sort
of thing happened

17:02.021 --> 17:03.789
when you and mom
first broke up, right?

17:03.789 --> 17:07.026
You didn't just, you know,
"heal" overnight?

17:07.026 --> 17:09.028
No.

17:09.028 --> 17:11.597
To some degree, maybe.

17:11.597 --> 17:12.999
[ Clears throat ]

17:12.999 --> 17:16.068
Look, Mace, sometimes it's
healthier to try to not focus

17:16.068 --> 17:20.039
on stuff that hurts,
you know?

17:20.039 --> 17:22.642
I guess,
but if you wanna come out

17:22.642 --> 17:26.379
on the other side, you have to
go through it, right?

17:26.379 --> 17:29.315
So that's why sometimes
I just put in my earbuds

17:29.315 --> 17:32.184
and listen to this.

17:32.184 --> 17:33.686
[ Lukas Graham's
"7 Years" plays ]

17:33.686 --> 17:37.990
♪ Once I was 7 years old
my momma told me ♪

17:37.990 --> 17:41.861
♪ "Go make yourself some friends
or you'll be lonely" ♪

17:41.861 --> 17:44.931
♪ Once I was 7 years old ♪

17:44.931 --> 17:49.902
♪♪

17:49.902 --> 17:51.871
♪ It was a big big world ♪
[ Sighs ]

17:51.871 --> 17:54.273
♪ But we thought
we were bigger ♪
I've never felt so small.

17:54.273 --> 17:56.208
♪ Pushing each other
to the limits ♪

17:56.208 --> 17:59.178
♪ We were learning quicker ♪
I know it's not
very manly, but...

17:59.178 --> 18:02.248
Hey.
Hey, no.

18:02.248 --> 18:04.350
You are more of a man
than I am.

18:04.350 --> 18:06.819
I'm serious.
You are.

18:06.819 --> 18:08.688
I really admire you, pal.

18:08.688 --> 18:10.022
Why?

18:10.022 --> 18:12.758
You know yourself.

18:12.758 --> 18:15.795
You know what you like,
what you don't like,

18:15.795 --> 18:18.764
and you're already brave enough
to be that person.

18:18.764 --> 18:22.001
And that's pretty awesome
for someone your age.

18:22.001 --> 18:23.302
And that may be

18:23.302 --> 18:25.204
the most important
survival skill there is,

18:25.204 --> 18:27.940
aside from knowing
how to purify water.

18:27.940 --> 18:29.408
That one's imperative.

18:35.715 --> 18:39.418
♪ Never rich so we were out to
make that steady figure ♪

18:39.418 --> 18:41.921
[ Together ]
♪ Once I was 11 years old ♪

18:41.921 --> 18:43.723
♪ My daddy told me ♪

18:43.723 --> 18:47.293
♪ Go get yourself a wife
or you'll be lonely ♪

18:47.293 --> 18:50.296
♪ Once I was 11 years old ♪

18:50.296 --> 18:52.298
♪ 11 years old ♪

18:52.298 --> 18:55.534
♪♪

18:55.534 --> 18:57.570
♪ I always had that dream ♪

18:57.570 --> 18:59.538
♪ Like my daddy before me ♪

18:59.538 --> 19:01.540
♪ So I started writing songs ♪

19:01.540 --> 19:03.542
♪ I started writing stories ♪

19:03.542 --> 19:05.544
♪ Something about that glory ♪

19:05.544 --> 19:07.546
♪ Just always seemed
to bore me ♪

19:07.546 --> 19:09.582
♪ 'Cause only those
I really love ♪

19:09.582 --> 19:10.649
♪ Will ever really know me ♪

19:10.649 --> 19:11.984
Lena: Wow!

19:11.984 --> 19:13.753
♪ Once I was 20 years old ♪
Look at this yard!

19:13.753 --> 19:17.890
And you opened the flooring,
and you got your own Ivan.

19:17.890 --> 19:20.493
Well, I told you I had somebody
bringing it.

19:20.493 --> 19:22.862
You really did everything
I asked.

19:22.862 --> 19:25.865
Well, I always was gonna do
what you asked,

19:25.865 --> 19:27.900
but just not when you asked.

19:27.900 --> 19:30.569
Yes, we both see I work better
when you leave me alone,

19:30.569 --> 19:34.140
so...let's do it
again soon, huh?

19:34.140 --> 19:35.808
It's really cute.

19:35.808 --> 19:36.776
Did you get that for me?

19:36.776 --> 19:38.110
[ Clears throat ] No.

19:38.110 --> 19:39.478
Really?

19:39.478 --> 19:40.713
It kinda feels like
you picked it for me.

19:40.713 --> 19:42.381
It's pink.
That's gender-typing.

19:42.381 --> 19:46.018
Besides, it's not...pink.

19:46.018 --> 19:48.187
No?

19:48.187 --> 19:49.455
[ Sighs ]

19:49.455 --> 19:51.691
It's more of a --
more of a borscht.

19:51.691 --> 19:53.325
Hmm.

19:53.325 --> 19:55.261
Feels like you picked it
for me.

19:59.598 --> 20:00.833
Martin: I got to hand it
to you,

20:00.833 --> 20:02.868
it's looking pretty good
around here.

20:02.868 --> 20:05.204
You really whipped those guys
into shape, huh?

20:05.204 --> 20:06.605
Actually, I didn't.

20:06.605 --> 20:09.175
I took your advice,
and I completely backed off.

20:09.175 --> 20:10.142
Hmm.

20:10.142 --> 20:12.344
Then I took Camille's advice.

20:12.344 --> 20:14.346
Well, actually,
it was the workers' advice.

20:14.346 --> 20:16.615
Long story short,
they did alright.

20:16.615 --> 20:17.883
Oh, they did more
than alright.

20:17.883 --> 20:20.886
And since the floors
are now breathing,

20:20.886 --> 20:22.621
the whole family gets
to camp out.

20:22.621 --> 20:24.023
Mason: Now drive it
in the ground right there.

20:24.023 --> 20:25.891
So you guys had fun
on your Play Day?

20:25.891 --> 20:29.428
Fun? No, no, we mostly cried
into a box of Wheat Thins.

20:29.428 --> 20:30.830
But it was cathartic.

20:30.830 --> 20:33.299
Our eyes were wet,
but our hair was dry.

20:33.299 --> 20:34.767
[ Sighs ]

20:34.767 --> 20:35.868
[ Paul Simon's "Mother
and Child Reunion" plays ]

20:35.868 --> 20:37.636
And speaking of which,

20:37.636 --> 20:41.107
whatever it is you're doing
with Mason, keep it up.

20:41.107 --> 20:42.575
He's a great kid,

20:42.575 --> 20:43.976
and I'm pretty sure I had
nothing to do with it.

20:43.976 --> 20:45.144
[ Chuckling ]

20:45.144 --> 20:46.679
Well, he was sorely missed
at home.

20:46.679 --> 20:48.981
Big curls to fill.
Mm.

20:48.981 --> 20:51.350
Will these keep overnight?

20:51.350 --> 20:53.519
Sure, I'll just set them
with some spray.

20:53.519 --> 20:55.421
Okay, thanks, Mom.

20:55.421 --> 20:56.856
Please tell me
that washes out.

20:56.856 --> 20:58.824
I know it doesn't seem like it
at this precise moment,

20:58.824 --> 21:00.993
but they really are a mix
of both of us.

21:00.993 --> 21:02.928
You think?
I think.

21:02.928 --> 21:04.864
I don't know.

21:04.864 --> 21:05.831
[ Chuckling ]

21:05.831 --> 21:07.867
Alright, well,
goodnight, curl.

21:07.867 --> 21:09.101
Goodnight, curl.

21:09.101 --> 21:10.336
♪ No, I would not give you
false hope ♪

21:10.336 --> 21:12.271
Alright, bedtime.

21:12.271 --> 21:13.572
♪ No ♪

21:13.572 --> 21:15.875
♪ On this strange
and mournful day ♪

21:15.875 --> 21:16.976
[ Groans ]

21:16.976 --> 21:20.880
♪ But the mother and child
reunion ♪

21:20.880 --> 21:21.780
♪ Is only... ♪

21:25.618 --> 21:27.353
[ Camera flashes ]
